# Link Performance Rule (<2s target, <800ms ideal)

Every navigation link in the app must feel instant. Follow these rules on every change:

## Link components (mandatory)
- **Server components**: use `AppLink` from `@/components/app-link` (never raw `next/link`)
- **Client components**: use `FastLink` from `@/components/fast-link` (hover + focus prefetch)
- Never use `router.push` for primary navigation — keep the declarative link graph

## Route loading
- Every route segment MUST have a `loading.tsx` with skeleton UI from `@/components/link-skeletons`
- Heavy client components (`QuestionList`, `SolutionViewer`, landing panels) MUST use `next/dynamic` + `Suspense`
- Solve pages MUST use `loadQuestionWithSiblings` — never import `allQuestions` for navigation

## Prefetch strategy
- Critical routes (`/curriculum`, `/questions`, `/dashboard`) are prefetched in root layout `<head>`
- `RoutePrefetcher` runs on idle in root layout
- Link-heavy grids use `PrefetchOnView` (IntersectionObserver)
- `NavigationProgress` prefetches on hover before click

## Data loading
- Subtopic pages: `loadSubtopic(slug)` only — one chunk per subtopic
- Question summaries for listings; full questions only on subtopic/solve pages
- Run `npm run sync-summaries` after adding subtopics

## Assets & caching
- `next.config.mjs`: keep `compress: true` and `optimizePackageImports` for lucide/framer-motion
- Service worker at `public/sw.js` caches navigations (stale-while-revalidate)
- Middleware sets long-cache headers for `/_next/static/`

## Verification (before merging)
```bash
cd wisest-maths-content
npm run build && npm run start
npm run perf:links   # all routes must be <2000ms
```

## Forbidden patterns
- Raw `<a href>` for internal routes
- Eager `allQuestions` import on solve/navigation paths
- New routes without `loading.tsx`
- Disabling `prefetch` without documented reason
